this place is a real time machine i used to visiting ppiptek almost every week due to indosat galileo hype 90s kid here so i remembered most of the exhibits there i had a impression that ppiptek was really fun back then as a child 2 decades later back to this place visiting as a parent bringing my 2 year old son as long as i could remember 70 of the exhibits with additions here there are still the same like i used to play as elementary student back then i jokingly told my husband that this place is an epitome of indonesias science condition undeveloped abandoned  many of the exhibits here are broken places are quite dim its very sad to see isc in such condition last week we had a chance to visited petrosains at klcc i realized comparing isc to petrosains isnt quite fair considering the entrance fee at isc is very cheap but both of them are stateowned petrosains under petronas and isc under brin hoping this place will get a huge maintenance revitalization a lot of fund is needed tho since higher education considered as tertriary maybe nah

historical places are always interesting to study or introduce to the next generation so that they dont forget the struggle of the heroes in liberating indonesia monjali or better known as the monumen jogja was erected to commemorate the event of the refunctioning of the city of yogyakarta as the capital of the republic of indonesia which was seized from the colonialists dutch this incident occurred on june 29 1949 the idea for establishing this museum was colonel soegiarto on june 29 1985 the monument began to be built then on july 6 1989 monjali was inaugurated by president soeharto the museum which is shaped like a tumpeng was built on an area of 49920 m2 with a height of 318 meters the monjali building consists of 3 floors the 1st floor contains 4 museum rooms the 2nd floor contains 10 dioramas and 40 reliefs and the 3rd floor is called the garba graha room the museums collection totals 1108 consisting of heraldry miniatures replicas vehicles firearms traditional weapons documentary photos army communications equipment medical equipment inventories statues archives lists of names of heroes reliefs dioramas and evocatives

the 2nd biggest karst site in the world located in maros about 15 hours by car from makassar indonesia no words can describe it is amazingly beautiful  the site offers a boat ride around walking path around the rice paddy fields climbing to caves and vast green karst mountains things to note  boat ride price differs by how many people onboard there is fixed price so you wont get scammed either way  come here on rainy season because thats when the rice paddy field gets all green not muddy for the best view  bring your sunblock or anything to cover you up because its getting hot at noon better come here early in morning so you get enough time to explore before its getting too hot to handle lol anyway if you ever visiting makassar dont skip this beaut

also known to many tourists as 500 lohan temple this temple is well known for their rows of lohan statues that seemingly looks at you no matter where you stand regardless of which direction there is at least one lohan statue that seems to be looking at you what many would not notice is that as this temple is located on top of a hill there is nice scenery at the entrance in addition as you walked on the left side of temple there are small stone block carvings that depict and tells the story of buddha as you walk on there is so much going on in this temple that if you look closely you might spend up to 30mins here but for those who doesnt like to read or admire the different lohan statues this place might take around 10mins max after the lohan statues walk on to the right side and there is a small store selling refreshments to drink and cup noodles to eat take some time to rest here and admire the peace and serenity of the temple head on to hang a lantern for blessing if you want location this place is near tanjung pinang but far from lagoi resorts about two hour drive from lagoi resorts tip could do a shopping trip at tanjung pinang and head here for sightseeing away from the busy streets for a short quiet moment
